<EFX_UNDERTAKING_AND_CONSENT>
<A NAME="FIS_UNDERTAKING_AND_CONSENT"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	Undertaking
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:3%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	Registrant undertakes to make available, in person or by telephone, representatives to respond to inquiries made by the Commission staff, and to furnish promptly, when requested to do so by the Commission
	staff, information relating to: the securities registered pursuant to Form 40-F; the securities in relation to which the obligation to file an annual report on Form 40-F arises; or transactions in said securities.
</FONT>
</P>
</EFX_UNDERTAKING_AND_CONSENT>
<EFX_CONTROL_AND_PROCEDURES>
<A NAME="FIS_CONTROL_AND_PROCEDURES"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	Controls and Procedures
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:3%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	The Registrant has established a system of controls and other procedures designed to ensure that information required to be disclosed in its periodic reports filed under the Securities Exchange Act of
	1934, as amended, is recorded, processed, summarized and reported within the time periods specified in the Securities and Exchange Commission&#146;s rules and forms. These disclosure controls and procedures have been evaluated under the direction of
	the Registrant&#146;s Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer as of the end of the Registrant&#146;s most recently completed fiscal year on September&nbsp;30, 2016. Based on such evaluations, the Chief Executive Officer and Chief
	Financial Officer have concluded that the disclosure controls and procedures are effective. No change was made in the Registrant&#146;s internal controls over financial reporting during the fiscal year ended September&nbsp;30, 2016 that has
	materially affected, or is reasonably likely to materially affect, the Registrant&#146;s internal control over financial reporting. No significant changes were made in the Registrant&#146;s internal controls or in other factors that could
	significantly affect these controls subsequent to the date of their evaluation.
</FONT>
</P>
</EFX_CONTROL_AND_PROCEDURES>
<EFX_AUDIT_COMMITTEE>
<A NAME="FIS_AUDIT_COMMITTEE"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	Audit Committee
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:3%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	The Audit and Risk Management Committee of the Board of Directors is composed entirely of unrelated directors who meet
	the independence and experience requirements of the New York Stock Exchange, the Toronto Stock Exchange, the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission rules and National Instrument 52-110, as amended.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:3%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	The Audit and Risk Management Committee is composed of Mr.&nbsp;Gilles Labb&eacute;, Chair of the Committee, and Messrs.
	Jean Brassard, Richard B. Evans, Timothy J. Hearn and Joakim Westh.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:3%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	The Registrant&#146;s Board of Directors
	has determined that the following members of the Audit and Risk Management Committee of the Board of Directors are &#147;audit committee financial experts&#148; within the meaning of paragraph (8)&nbsp;of General Instruction B to Form 40-F:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; MARGIN-LEFT:12%">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	&#150;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Gilles Labb&eacute;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:3%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	Please refer to the Registrant&#146;s Management Proxy Circular dated December&nbsp;12, 2016 under the heading
<I>
	Nominees for Election as Directors
</I>
	for a brief summary of Mr.&nbsp;Labb&eacute;&#146;s relevant experience.
</FONT>
</P>
</EFX_AUDIT_COMMITTEE>
<EFX_ACCOUNTANT_FEES>
<A NAME="FIS_ACCOUNTANT_FEES"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	Principal Accountant
	Fees and Services
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:3%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	In order to satisfy itself as to the independence of the external auditors, the Audit
	and Risk Management Committee has adopted an auditor independence policy which covers (a)&nbsp;the services that may and may not be performed by the external auditors, (b)&nbsp;the governance procedures to be followed prior to retaining services
	from the external auditors, and (c)&nbsp;the responsibilities of the key participants. The following is a summary of the material provisions of the policy.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<I>
	Performance of Services
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:3%">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	Services are either acceptable services or
	prohibited services.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:3%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	The acceptable services are (a)&nbsp;audit and review of financial statements,
	(b)&nbsp;prospectus work, (c)&nbsp;audit of pension plans, (d)&nbsp;special audits on control procedures, (e)&nbsp;tax planning services on mergers and acquisitions activities, (f)&nbsp;due diligence relating to mergers and acquisitions,
	(g)&nbsp;tax services related to transfer pricing, (h)&nbsp;sales tax planning and returns, (i)&nbsp;research and interpretation related to taxation, (j)&nbsp;research relating to accounting issues, (k)&nbsp;tax planning services,
	(l)&nbsp;preparation of tax returns and (m)&nbsp;all other services that are not prohibited services.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="CENTER">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	-&nbsp;2&nbsp;-
</FONT>
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage3"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D228504D40F_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:3%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	The prohibited services are (a)&nbsp;bookkeeping services, (b)&nbsp;design
	and implementation of financial information systems, (c)&nbsp;appraisal or valuation services or fairness opinions, (d)&nbsp;actuarial services, (e)&nbsp;internal audit services, (f)&nbsp;management functions, (g)&nbsp;human resources functions,
	(h)&nbsp;broker-dealer services, (i)&nbsp;legal services, (j)&nbsp;services based on contingency fees and (k)&nbsp;expert services.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<I>
	Governance Procedures
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:3%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	The following control procedures
	are applicable when considering whether to retain the external auditors&#146; services:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:3%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	For all services
	falling within the permitted services category, whether they are audit or non-audit services, a request for approval must be submitted to the Audit and Risk Management Committee through the Executive
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	Vice-President
</FONT>
	and Chief Financial Officer prior to engaging the auditors to perform the services.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:3%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	In the interests of efficiency, certain permitted services are pre-approved quarterly by the Audit and Risk Management Committee and thereafter only require approval by the Executive Vice-President and
	Chief Financial Officer as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PX;MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	&#149;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	The Audit and Risk Management Committee can pre-approve envelopes for certain services to
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	pre-determined
</FONT>
	dollar limits on a quarterly basis;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	&#149;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	Once pre-approved by the Audit and Risk Management Committee, the Executive Vice-President and Chief Financial Officer may approve the services
	prior to the engagement;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	&#149;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	For services not covered by the pre-approved envelopes and for costs in excess of the pre-approved amounts, separate requests for approval must be
	submitted to the Audit and Risk Management Committee; and
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	&#149;
</FONT>

<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	At each quarterly meeting of the Audit and Risk Management Committee, a consolidated summary of all fees by service type is presented including a
	breakdown of fees incurred within each of the pre-approved envelopes.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<EFX_CODE_OF_ETHICS>
<A NAME="FIS_CODE_OF_ETHICS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	Code of Ethics
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:3%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	In addition to its Code of Ethics and Business Conduct (which incorporates the CGI Anti-Corruption Policy) that applies
	to all the Registrant&#146;s employees, officers and directors, the Registrant has adopted an Executive Code of Conduct that applies specifically to the Registrant&#146;s principal executive officer, principal financial officer, principal accounting
	officer or controller, or other persons performing similar functions (collectively, the &#147;Officers&#148;). The Executive Code of Conduct is designed to deter wrongdoing and to promote:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PX;MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="12%">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	&#150;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	Honest and ethical conduct, including the ethical handling of actual or apparent conflicts of interest between personal and professional
	relationships;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="12%">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	&#150;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	Full, fair, accurate, timely, and understandable disclosure in reports and documents that the Registrant files with, or submits to, the Securities
	and Exchange Commission and in other public communications made by the Registrant;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="12%">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	&#150;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	Compliance with applicable governmental laws, rules and regulations;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="12%">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	&#150;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	The prompt internal reporting of violations of the Executive Code of Conduct to an appropriate person or persons identified in the Executive Code of
	Conduct; and
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="12%">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	&#150;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="TOP">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	Accountability for adherence to the Executive Code of Conduct.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:3%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	The Registrant&#146;s Executive Code of Conduct and its Code of Ethics and Business Conduct (which incorporates the
	CGI&nbsp;Anti-Corruption Policy) have been posted on the Registrant&#146;s website at http://www.cgi.com.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:3%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	The
	Board of Directors monitors compliance with the Executive Code of Conduct and the Code of Ethics and Business Conduct (which incorporates the CGI Anti-Corruption Policy) and, under the Board of Directors charter, is responsible for any waivers of
	such codes&#146; provisions granted to directors or Officers. No such waivers have been granted to date.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	Corporate Governance Practices
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:3%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	CGI&#146;s corporate governance practices conform to those followed by U.S. domestic companies under the
<I>
	New York Stock Exchange
</I>
	listing standards.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	Off-balance sheet arrangements
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	The Registrant does not enter into off-balance sheet financing as a matter of practice except for the use of operating
	leases for office space, computer equipment and vehicles as well as the sale of accounts receivable, none of which are off-balance sheet arrangements within the meaning of paragraph (11)&nbsp;of General Instruction B to Form&nbsp;40-F.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:3%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	As disclosed in note 29 to the Registrant&#146;s Consolidated Financial Statements, in the normal course of business, the
	Registrant enters into agreements that may provide for indemnification and guarantees to counterparties in transactions such as consulting and outsourcing services, business divestitures, lease agreements and financial obligations. These
	indemnification undertakings and guarantees may require the Company to compensate counterparties for costs and losses incurred as a result of various events, including breaches of representations and warranties, intellectual property right
	infringement, claims that may arise while providing services or as a result of litigation that may be suffered by counterparties. The nature of most indemnification undertakings prevent the Registrant from making a reasonable estimate of the maximum
	potential amount the Registrant could be required to pay counterparties, as the agreements do not specify a maximum amount and the amounts are dependent upon the outcome of future contingent events, the nature and likelihood of which cannot be
	determined at this time. The Registrant does not expect that any sum it may have to pay in connection with these guarantees will have a materially adverse effect on its Consolidated Financial Statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="CENTER">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	-&nbsp;4&nbsp;-
</FONT>
</P>

<EFX_CORPORATE_STRUCTURE>
<A NAME="FIS_CORPORATE_STRUCTURE"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:18PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_1">
</A>
	CORPORATE STRUCTURE
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:14PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_2">
</A>
	Incorporation and Registered Office
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	CGI&nbsp;Group&nbsp;Inc. (the &#147;Company&#148;,
	&#147;CGI&#148;, &#147;we&#148;, &#147;us&#148; or &#147;our&#148;) was incorporated on September&nbsp;29, 1981 under Part&nbsp;IA of the Companies Act (Quebec), predecessor to the Business Corporations Act (Quebec), which came into force on
	February&nbsp;14, 2011 and which now governs the Company. The Company continued the activities of Conseillers en gestion et informatique CGI inc., which was originally founded in 1976. The executive and registered offices of the Company are situated
	at 1350
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	Ren&eacute;-L&eacute;vesque
</FONT>
	Blvd. West, 25
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	th
</SUP>
	&nbsp;Floor, Montreal, Quebec, Canada, H3G 1T4. CGI became a public company on December&nbsp;17, 1986,
	upon completing an initial public offering of its Class&nbsp;A subordinate voting shares (&#147;Class&nbsp;A subordinate voting shares&#148;).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:14PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_3">
</A>
	Subsidiaries
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The activities of the Company are conducted either directly or through subsidiaries. The table below lists the principal subsidiaries of the Company as
	at September&nbsp;30, 2016, each of which is directly or indirectly wholly-owned by the Company. Certain subsidiaries whose total assets did not represent more than 10% of the Company&#146;s consolidated assets or whose revenues did not represent
	more than 10% of the Company&#146;s consolidated revenues as at September&nbsp;30, 2016
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	1
</SUP>
	, have been omitted. The subsidiaries that have been omitted represent, as a group, less than 20% of the
	consolidated assets and revenues of the Company as at September&nbsp;30, 2016. This table omits subsidiaries whose primary role is to hold investments in other CGI subsidiary entities.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:14PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_4">
</A>
	Capital Structure
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company&#146;s authorized share capital consists of an unlimited number of Class&nbsp;A subordinate voting shares carrying one vote per share and an
	unlimited number of Class&nbsp;B shares (multiple voting) (&#147;Class&nbsp;B shares&#148;) carrying 10&nbsp;votes per share, all without par value, of which, as of December&nbsp;12, 2016, 270,316,749 Class&nbsp;A subordinate voting shares and
	32,852,748&nbsp;Class&nbsp;B shares, were issued and outstanding. These shares represent respectively 45.14% and 54.86% of the aggregate voting rights attached to the outstanding Class&nbsp;A subordinate voting shares and Class&nbsp;B shares. Two
	classes of preferred shares also form part of CGI&#146;s authorized capital: an unlimited number of First Preferred Shares, issuable in series, and an unlimited number of Second Preferred Shares, also issuable in series. As of December&nbsp;12, 2016
	there were no preferred shares outstanding.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company incorporates by reference the disclosure contained under the headings
<I>
	Class
</I>
<I>
</I>
<I>
	&nbsp;A Subordinate Voting Shares and Class
</I>
<I>
</I>
<I>
	&nbsp;B Shares
</I>
	on pages&nbsp;3 to 5, and
<I>
	First Preferred Shares
</I>
	and
<I>
	Second Preferred Shares
</I>
	on page 5 of CGI&#146;s Management Proxy Circular dated
	December&nbsp;12, 2016 which was filed with Canadian securities regulatory authorities and which is available at
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" COLOR="#E67386">
<U>
	www.sedar.com
</U>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
	and on CGI&#146;s web site
	at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" COLOR="#E67386">
<U>

</U>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
	.
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_7">
</A>
	Normal Course Issuer Bid and Share Repurchases
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<I>
</I>
	On January&nbsp;27, 2016, CGI announced that it was renewing its normal course issuer bid (&#147;NCIB&#148;) to repurchase up to 10% of the
	Company&#146;s public float of its issued and outstanding Class&nbsp;A subordinate voting shares during the normal course issuer bid term that commenced on February&nbsp;11, 2016 and will expire on February&nbsp;3, 2017 at the latest. On
	December&nbsp;2, 2016, the Company entered into a specific share repurchase program with a third party, which will form part of the NCIB. See
<I>
	Description of CGI&#146;s Business &#150; Significant developments of the Three Most Recent Fiscal Years
	&#150; Fiscal Year ended September&nbsp;30, 2016 &#150; Share Repurchase Program later in this document.
</I>
</P>

<EFX_BUSINESS>
<A NAME="FIS_BUSINESS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:18PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_15">
</A>
	DESCRIPTION OF CGI&#146;S BUSINESS
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:14PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_16">
</A>
	Mission, Vision and Strategy
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The mission of CGI is to help its clients with professional services of outstanding quality, competence and objectivity, delivering the best solutions to
	fully satisfy client objectives in information technology (&#147;IT&#148;), business processes and management. In all we do, we foster a culture of partnership, intrapreneurship and integrity, building a global IT and business process services
	company.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	CGI is unique compared to most companies. We not only have a vision, but also a dream: &#147;To create an environment in which we enjoy
	working together and, as owners, contribute to building a company we can be proud of.&#148; This dream has motivated us since our founding in 1976 and drives our vision: &#147;To be a global, world-class IT and business process services leader
	helping our clients succeed.&#148;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	In pursuing this dream and vision, CGI has been highly disciplined throughout its history in executing a
	&#147;Build and Buy&#148; profitable growth strategy comprised of four pillars that combine profitable organic growth (&#147;Build&#148;) and accretive acquisitions (&#147;Buy&#148;):
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#9679;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="TOP">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<B>
	Pillar 1
</B>
	: Smaller contract wins, renewals and extensions;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#9679;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="TOP">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<B>
	Pillar 2
</B>
	: Large, long-term transformational outsourcing contracts;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#9679;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="TOP">

	Pillar 3
</B>
	:
<B>
</B>
	Small firm or niche player acquisitions; and
</P>
</TD>

<B>
	Pillar 4
</B>
	: Large, transformational acquisitions.
</P>
</TD>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">

<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D228504D40F_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/12/21/0001193125-16-800302_G228504ANNINFO.JPG" ALT="LOGO">
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The first two pillars relate to driving profitable organic growth through the pursuit of contracts-both
	large and small-with new and existing clients in our targeted industries.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The last two pillars focus on growth through niche and large acquisitions.
	We identify niche acquisitions through a strategic qualification process that systematically searches for targets to strengthen our local proximity in metro markets, our industry expertise and enhance our services and solutions. We also pursue large
	acquisitions to further expand our geographic presence and critical mass, which enables us to compete for large outsourcing contracts and broaden our client relationships. CGI will continue to be a consolidator in the IT services industry.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Since 1976, our professionals have been working toward the same dream and vision. Today, with a presence in hundreds of global locations and more than
	$10&nbsp;billion in revenue, our aspiration is to double our size over a five to seven year period.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	CGI&#146;s Mission, Vision, Dream and Values are
	explained in the Company&#146;s Fundamental Texts,
<I>
</I>
	which
<I>
</I>
	are annexed as Appendix&nbsp;A, and are available on the Company&#146;s web site at
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" COLOR="#E67386">
<U>
	www.cgi.com
</U>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:12PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
	Executing our strategy
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	CGI&#146;s strategy is executed through a unique business model that combines client proximity with an extensive global delivery network to deliver the
	following benefits:
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#9679;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="TOP">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<B>
	Local responsiveness and accountability
</B>
	:
<B>
</B>
	We live and work near our clients to provide a high level of
	responsiveness. Our local CGI teams speak our clients&#146; language, understand their business environment, and collaborate to meet their goals and advance their business.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#9679;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="TOP">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<B>
	Global reach
</B>
	: Our local presence is complemented by an expansive global delivery network that ensures our clients
	have 24/7 access to
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	best-fit
</FONT>
	digital capabilities and resources to meet their
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	end-to-end
</FONT>
</FONT>
	needs.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#9679;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="TOP">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<B>
	Committed experts
</B>
	: One of our key strategic goals is to be our clients&#146; expert of choice. To achieve this,
	we invest in recruiting professionals with extensive industry, business and technology expertise, particularly in high-demand areas, such as agile services, robotics process automation, cloud, mobile computing, cybersecurity, data analytics and the
	Internet of Things. In addition, a majority of CGI professionals are also shareholders, providing an added level of commitment to the success of our clients.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<B>
	Comprehensive quality processes
</B>
	: CGI&#146;s investment in quality frameworks and rigorous client satisfaction
	assessments has resulted in a consistent track record of on-time and within-budget project delivery.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:14PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_17">
</A>
	Business Structure
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company&#146;s operations are managed through the following seven operating segments, referred to as our
	Strategic Business Units, namely: United States of America (&#147;U.S.&#148;); Nordics; Canada; France (including Luxembourg and Morocco) (&#147;France&#148;); United Kingdom (&#147;U.K.&#148;); Eastern, Central and Southern Europe (primarily
	Netherlands and Germany) (&#147;ECS&#148;); and Asia Pacific (including Australia, India and the Philippines) (&#147;Asia Pacific&#148;). For additional information on our operating segments, please refer to sections&nbsp;3.4 and 3.6 of CGI&#146;s
	Management&#146;s Discussion and Analysis for Fiscal Year 2016 and to note&nbsp;27 of our audited consolidated financial statements for the years ended September&nbsp;30, 2016 and 2015, which were filed with Canadian securities regulatory
	authorities and are available at
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" COLOR="#E67386">
<U>
	www.sedar.com
</U>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
	and on CGI&#146;s web site at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" COLOR="#E67386">
<U>
	www.cgi.com
</U>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
	.
</FONT>
</P>

</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	CGI has long and focused practices in all of its core industries, providing clients with a partner that is not only
	expert in IT, but expert in their industries. This combination of business knowledge and digital technology expertise allows us to help our clients adapt as their industries change and, in the process, allows us to evolve the industries in which we
	operate.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Our targeted industries include: government, financial services, health, utilities, telecommunications, oil&nbsp;&amp; gas, manufacturing,
	retail&nbsp;&amp; consumer services, transportation and post and logistics. While these represent our go to market industry targets, we group these industries into the following: government; financial services; health; telecommunications&nbsp;&amp;
	utilities; and manufacturing, retail&nbsp;&amp; distribution (&#147;MRD&#148;).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	As the move toward digitalization continues to increase across
	industries, CGI partners with clients to support their strategic initiatives. We provide extensive expertise to guide them in becoming customer-centric digital organizations.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
<B>
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/12/21/0001193125-16-800302_G228504BOTTOM.JPG" ALT="LOGO">
</B>
</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:7PT" ALIGN="CENTER">
<TR>

</TD>

<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>

<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D228504D40F_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/12/21/0001193125-16-800302_G228504ANNINFO.JPG" ALT="LOGO">
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:12PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_20">
</A>
	Intangible Properties
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	We own and use various intangible assets which include, without limitation, brand names, trademarks, patents and patent applications, copyrights and
	copyrighted material, domain names, customer lists,
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	know-how,
</FONT>
	tools, techniques, software, processes and methodologies. We derive value through the use of these assets in our business activities and they are
	central to our operations.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Our success depends, in part, on our ability to protect our proprietary intangible assets that we use to provide our
	services. We rely on a combination of contractual and licensing agreements and trademarks, copyright and patent laws to protect these assets against infringement.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Our general practice is to pursue trademark, patent, copyright, or other appropriate intellectual property protection that is timely and necessary to
	protect and leverage our intellectual assets for the longest possible period. We will continue to seek intellectual property protection for our technology, software, methodologies, processes,
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	know-how,
</FONT>
	tools,
	techniques and other proprietary information and that throughout the various countries within which CGI operates.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:12PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_21">
</A>
	Human Resources
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	As of September&nbsp;30, 2016, CGI had approximately 68,000&nbsp;employees, whom we refer to as members. In order to encourage the high degree of
	commitment necessary to ensure the quality and continuity of client service, CGI offers its members the right to acquire Class&nbsp;A subordinate voting shares pursuant to a
<I>
	Share Purchase Plan
</I>
	. Among the countries in which we currently offer
	the Share Purchase Plan, approximately 52,000 of our members own Class&nbsp;A subordinate voting shares. The Company also has a
<I>
	Profit Participation Plan
</I>
	which reinforces our ownership culture by distributing a portion of the Company&#146;s
	profits based on business performance.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:12PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_22">
</A>
	Specialized Skills and Knowledge
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The skills, expertise and competencies&nbsp;required by clients in the IT industry are constantly evolving. CGI strives to be one step ahead and adopts a
	proactive approach, not only by recruiting engaged and skilled professionals but more importantly developing and retaining them to meet our clients&#146; needs.&nbsp;In addition to training and development activities&nbsp;and participation in
	professional associations, our talent management strategy includes stretch project assignments (local and abroad), job shadowing, coaching, mentoring and access to leadership and core competencies development programs through CGI&#146;s Leadership
	Institute. Over the years, we have put in place multiple initiatives to ensure we are able to meet our clients&#146; needs, fulfill our business plans, maintain and develop professionals&nbsp;of the highest calibre for the benefits of our clients,
	members and shareholders.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:12PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_23">
</A>
	CGI Offices and Global Delivery Model
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	CGI serves its clients from global delivery centers located on four continents. These delivery centers enable CGI to provide its clients with the right
	mix of onshore, near-shore and
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	off-shore
</FONT>
	IT services that best suits their business needs.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">

</P>

	All of CGI&#146;s offices are located in rented premises with the exception of the following properties, which are owned by CGI: one property in Belton,
	Texas; one property in Lebanon, Virginia where the land is leased with a right to acquire; one property in Phoenix, Arizona which is a data center; one property in Montreal, Quebec, which is a data center; one data center in Mississauga, Ontario;
	one property in Riihim&auml;ki, Finland; one office building in Mumbai, India that is built on land that we lease; two properties in Odivelas, Portugal; one property in Brom&ouml;lla, Sweden; and two properties in Bridgend, United Kingdom, one of
	which is an office building and the other of which is a parcel of land.

<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D228504D40F_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/12/21/0001193125-16-800302_G228504ANNINFO.JPG" ALT="LOGO">
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:12PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_24">
</A>
	Commercial Alliances
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	CGI currently has commercial alliance agreements with various business partners. These
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	non-exclusive
</FONT>
	commercial
	agreements with hardware and software providers allow the Company to provide its clients with high quality technology, often on advantageous commercial terms. CGI&#146;s business partners include prominent hardware and software providers.
<B>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:12PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_25">
</A>
	Quality Processes
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	CGI&#146;s ISO 9001 certified operations that are reflected in its management frameworks ensure that its clients&#146; objectives are clearly defined,
	that projects are properly scoped and that the necessary resources are applied to meet objectives. These processes ensure that clients&#146; requirements drive CGI&#146;s solutions. Clients are constantly kept informed; their degree of satisfaction
	is regularly measured and part of the incentive compensation of CGI managers is linked to the results.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	In 1993, the Company began working towards
	obtaining ISO 9001 certification for the portion of its operations covered by its
<I>
	Project Management Framework
</I>
	. CGI&#146;s Quebec City office was granted ISO&nbsp;9001 certification in June 1994, which allowed CGI to become North
	America&#146;s first organization in the IT consulting field to receive ISO 9001 certification for the way in which it managed projects. Since 1995, CGI expanded the ISO 9001 certification throughout its Canadian, U.S. and international offices as
	well as its corporate headquarters. Over the past several years, in the context of CGI&#146;s high growth rate, its ISO certified quality system has been a key ingredient in spreading its culture, in part because it helps to integrate new members
	successfully.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	As clients grow and IT projects become increasingly complex, CGI strives to further refine its quality processes while allowing them
	to branch out across all its activities. CGI&#146;s enhanced quality system of which the
<I>
	Client Partnership Management Framework
</I>
	forms part, is simpler and provides the Company&#146;s business units with greater autonomy in a context of
	decentralized activities. One of CGI&#146;s key focus areas remains the successful management of client relationships, leading to long-term partnerships. CGI applications development centers in Mumbai, Hyderabad, Chennai and Bangalore in India, have
	achieved SEI CMMi DEV Level&nbsp;5 quality certification and ISO 27001 security management system certification.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	CGI also obtained ISO 9001
	certification for the application of its
<I>
	Member Partnership Management Framework
</I>
	in its operations and, in 2004, we similarly obtained ISO 9001 certification for the portion of our operations covered by our
<I>
	Shareholder Partnership
	Management Framework
</I>
	(&#147;SPMF&#148;). The SPMF structures the processes and information flows between CGI and its shareholders as well as with the investment community.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	CGI now holds ISO quality certification for the management of its partnerships with each of its three major stakeholder groups, namely clients, members
	and shareholders.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
<B>
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/12/21/0001193125-16-800302_G228504BOTTOM.JPG" ALT="LOGO">
</B>
</P>

	&nbsp;

<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
</TD>

<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D228504D40F_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/12/21/0001193125-16-800302_G228504ANNINFO.JPG" ALT="LOGO">
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:14PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_26">
</A>
	The IT Services Industry
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:12PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_27">
</A>
	Trends and Outlook
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Although the current state of the economy makes it difficult to predict future trends in IT spending, CGI intends to continue its &#147;Build and
	Buy&#148; growth strategy, expanding both through profitable organic growth (Build) and through accretive acquisitions (Buy). Today more than ever, technology is essential to enabling and driving change for both businesses and governments. Any new
	service, program or efficiency improvement brings a need for additional IT.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	As part of our annual strategic planning activities in 2016, we held
	1,024
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	face-to-face
</FONT>
</FONT>
	interviews with our executive-level clients. A few key trends and priorities, common across industries and geographies emerged from these
	conversations: the need for digital transformation brought about by an increasingly mobile and digital world; the ever increasing regulatory compliance requirements not only in finance but in a broad range of domains; and the growth in cybersecurity
	threats.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	These trends, along with the rise of technology innovation in areas such as analytics and the &#147;Internet of Things&#148;, combine to
	create a need to ensure that IT is more secure than ever, from infrastructures to applications. Achieving this requires significant investments and understanding that IT is not a commodity but a crucial asset to be protected.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Budget pressures and the need to improve performance remain an ongoing trend across industries, thereby presenting opportunities that the Company has
	successfully exploited in the past. We believe that the potential in IT and business process services outsourcing remains enormous. CGI has from time to time commissioned a study from
<I>
	International Data Corp.
</I>
	(&#147;IDC&#148;) which provides
	CGI with insight as to spending on IT and business process services in Canada, the United States and Europe.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	According to IDC&#146;s research
	conducted in 2015, the IT domain spending was estimated to be US$690&nbsp;billion in the U.S. and US$613&nbsp;billion in Europe (in countries where CGI is present) and US$74&nbsp;billion in Canada. These numbers exclude the value of services already
	outsourced and indicate a large untapped potential market for outsourcing services.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:14PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_28">
</A>
	Competitive Environment
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	In today&#146;s digital era, there is a competitive urgency for organizations across industries to become digital in a sustainable way.
	The pressure is on to modernize legacy assets and connect them to digital business and operating models. Central to this massive transformation is the evolving role of technology. Traditionally viewed as an enabler, technology is now being
	recognized as a business driver. The promise of digital creates an enormous opportunity to transform organizations
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	end-to-end,
</FONT>
</FONT>
	and CGI is well-positioned to serve as a
	digital partner and expert of choice. We are working with clients across the globe to implement digital strategies, roadmaps and solutions that revolutionize the customer/citizen experience, drive the launch of new products and services, and deliver
	efficiencies and cost savings.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	As the demand for digitalization increases, competition within the global IT industry is intensifying. CGI&#146;s
	competition comprises a variety of players; from niche companies providing specialized services and software, to global,
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	end-to-end
</FONT>
</FONT>
	IT service providers, to large
	consulting firms. All of these players are competing to deliver some or all of the services we provide. Many factors distinguish the industry leaders, including the following:
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#9679;
</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="TOP">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
	Industry and technology expertise;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	CGI compares very favourably with the competition with respect to all of these factors. We are not only delivering all of the capabilities clients need
	to compete in a digital world, but the immediate results and long-term value they expect. We are helping clients to better run, change and grow their businesses providing a competitive differentiator.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:12PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_29">
</A>
	Significant Developments of the Three Most Recent Fiscal Years
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:12PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_30">
</A>
	Key Performance Measures
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company reports its financial results in accordance with International Financial Reporting Standards (&#147;IFRS&#148;). However, we use a
	combination of financial measures, ratios, and
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	non-GAAP
</FONT>
	measures to assess our Company&#146;s performance. The
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	non-GAAP
</FONT>
	measures used to report our financial results do
	not have any standardized meaning prescribed by IFRS and are therefore unlikely to be comparable to similar measures presented by other issuers. These measures should be considered as supplemental in nature and not as a substitute for the related
	financial information prepared in accordance with IFRS. The table below summarizes our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	non-GAAP
</FONT>
	measures and most relevant key performance measures:
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<A NAME="FIS_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE_16"></A>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT" ALIGN="CENTER">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="13%">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" WIDTH="3%">
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="84%">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<B>
	Profitability&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</B>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<I>
	Adjusted EBIT
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	(non-GAAP)
</FONT>
</I>
	&#150; is a measure of earnings excluding restructuring
	costs, net finance costs and income tax expense as these items are not directly related to the cost of operations. Management believes this measure is useful to investors as it best reflects the Company&#146;s operating profitability and allows for
	better comparability from period to period as well as to trend analysis in our operations. A reconciliation of the adjusted EBIT to its closest IFRS measure can be found in section&nbsp;3.7 of CGI&#146;s Management&#146;s Discussion and Analysis for
	Fiscal Year 2016.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-SIZE:1PT">
<TD HEIGHT="8">
</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<I>
	Net earnings
</I>
	&#150; is a measure of earnings generated for shareholders.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-SIZE:1PT">
<TD HEIGHT="8">
</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<I>
	Diluted earnings per share
</I>
	&#150; is a measure of earnings generated for shareholders on a per share basis, assuming all
	dilutive elements are exercised.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-SIZE:1PT">
<TD HEIGHT="8">
</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<I>
	Net earnings excluding specific items
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	(non-GAAP)
</FONT>
</I>
	&#150; is a measure of net earnings
	excluding certain items not considered by management to be part of the day to day operations. By excluding these items, it provides a better evaluation of operating performance using the same measures as management. Management believes that, as a
	result, the investors are afforded greater transparency in assessing the true operation performance of the Company also providing better comparability from period to period. A reconciliation of the net earnings excluding specific items
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	(non-GAAP)
</FONT>
	to its closest IFRS measure can be found in section 3.8.3. of CGI&#146;s Management&#146;s Discussion and Analysis for Fiscal Year 2016.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-SIZE:1PT">
<TD HEIGHT="8">
</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<I>
	Basic and diluted earnings per share excluding specific items
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	(non-GAAP)
</FONT>
</I>
	&#150; is
	defined as the net earnings excluding specific items on a per share basis. Management believes that this measure is useful to investors as it best reflects the Company&#146;s operating profitability on a per share basis and allows for better
	comparability from
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT" ALIGN="CENTER">

<TD WIDTH="85%">

<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">

</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
	period to period. The basic and diluted earnings per share reported in accordance with IFRS can be found on section 3.8 of CGI&#146;s
	Management&#146;s Discussion and Analysis for Fiscal Year&nbsp;2016, while the basic and diluted earnings per share excluding specific items can be found in section 3.8.3. of CGI&#146;s Management&#146;s Discussion and Analysis for Fiscal Year
	2016.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-SIZE:1PT">
<TD HEIGHT="8">
</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<B>
	Liquidity&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</B>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<I>
	Cash provided by operating activities
</I>
	&#150; is a measure of cash generated from managing our
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	day-to-day
</FONT>
</FONT>
	business operations. We believe strong operating cash flow is indicative of financial flexibility, allowing us to execute our Company&#146;s
	strategy.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-SIZE:1PT">
<TD HEIGHT="8">
</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<I>
	Days sales outstanding (&#147;DSO&#148;)
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	(non-GAAP)
</FONT>
</I>
	&#150; is the average number of
	days needed to convert our trade receivables and work in progress into cash. DSO is obtained by subtracting deferred revenue from trade accounts receivable and work in progress; the result is divided by the quarter&#146;s revenue over 90&nbsp;days.
	Deferred revenue is net of the fair value adjustments on revenue-generating contracts established upon business combination. Management tracks this metric closely to ensure timely collection, healthy liquidity, and is committed to a DSO target of
	45&nbsp;days or less. We believe this measure is useful to investors as it demonstrates the Company&#146;s ability to timely convert its trade receivables and work in progress into cash.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-SIZE:1PT">
<TD HEIGHT="8">
</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<B>
	Growth
</B>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<I>
	Constant currency growth
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	(non-GAAP)
</FONT>
</I>
	&#150; is a measure of revenue growth before
	foreign currency impacts. This growth is calculated by translating current period results in local currency using the conversion rates in the equivalent period from the prior year. Management believes that it is helpful to adjust revenue to exclude
	the impact of currency fluctuations to facilitate
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	period-to-period
</FONT>
</FONT>
	comparisons of business performance. We believe that this measure is useful to investors for the same
	reason.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-SIZE:1PT">
<TD HEIGHT="8">
</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<I>
	Backlog
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	(non-GAAP)
</FONT>
</I>
	&#150; includes new contract wins, extensions and renewals
	(&#147;bookings&#148;)
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	(non-GAAP),
</FONT>
	partially offset by the backlog consumed during the period as a result of client work performed and adjustments related to the volume, cancellation and the impact of foreign
	currencies to our existing contracts. Backlog incorporates estimates from management that are subject to change. Management tracks this measure as it is a key indicator of management&#146;s best estimate of revenue to be realized in the future and
	believes that this measure is useful to investors for the same reason.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-SIZE:1PT">
<TD HEIGHT="8">
</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<I>
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	Book-to-bill
</FONT>
</FONT>
	ratio
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	(non-GAAP)
</FONT>
</I>
	&#150; is a measure of the proportion of the value of our bookings to our revenue in the period. This metric allows management to monitor the Company&#146;s business development efforts to
	ensure we grow our backlog and our business over time and believes that this measure is useful to investors for the same reason. Management remains committed to maintaining a target ratio greater than 100% over a trailing
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	12-month
</FONT>
	period. Management believes that the longer period is a more representative measure as the services and contract type, size and timing of bookings could cause this measurement to fluctuate significantly if
	taken for only a three-month period.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-SIZE:1PT">
<TD HEIGHT="8">
</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<B>
	Capital&nbsp;Structure
</B>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<I>
	Net debt
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	(non-GAAP)
</FONT>
</I>
	&#150; is obtained by subtracting from our debt our cash and cash
	equivalents, short-term investments, long-term investments and fair value of foreign currency derivative financial instruments related to debt. Management uses the net debt metric to monitor the Company&#146;s financial leverage. We believe that
	this metric is useful to investors as it provides insight into our financial strength. A reconciliation of net debt to its closest IFRS measure can be found in section 4.5 of CGI&#146;s Management&#146;s Discussion and Analysis for Fiscal Year
	2016.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>

<B>
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/12/21/0001193125-16-800302_G228504BOTTOM.JPG" ALT="LOGO">
</B>
</P>

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="34%">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">

<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D228504D40F_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/12/21/0001193125-16-800302_G228504ANNINFO.JPG" ALT="LOGO">
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT" ALIGN="CENTER">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="14%">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" WIDTH="1%">
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="85%">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-SIZE:1PT">
<TD HEIGHT="8">
</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<I>
	Net debt to capitalization ratio
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	(non-GAAP)
</FONT>
</I>
	&#150; is a measure of our level of
	financial leverage and is obtained by dividing the net debt by the sum of shareholder&#146;s equity and debt. Management uses the net debt to capitalization metric to monitor the proportion of debt versus capital used to finance our operations and
	to assess the Company&#146;s financial strength. We believe that this metric is useful to investors as it provides insight into our financial strength.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-SIZE:1PT">
<TD HEIGHT="8">
</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<I>
	Return on equity (&#147;ROE&#148;)
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	(non-GAAP)
</FONT>
</I>
	&#150; is a measure of the rate of
	return on the ownership interest of our shareholders and is calculated as the proportion of earnings for the last 12&nbsp;months over the last four quarters&#146; average equity. Management looks at ROE to measure its efficiency at generating
	earnings for the Company&#146;s shareholders and how well the Company uses the invested funds to generate earnings growth. We believe that this measure is useful to investors for the same reasons.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-SIZE:1PT">
<TD HEIGHT="8">
</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:10PT">
<I>
	Return on invested capital (&#147;ROIC&#148;)
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	(non-GAAP)
</FONT>
</I>
	&#150; is a measure of the
	Company&#146;s efficiency at allocating the capital under its control to profitable investments and is calculated as the proportion of the
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	after-tax
</FONT>
	adjusted EBIT for the last 12&nbsp;months, over the last
	four quarters&#146; average invested capital, which is defined as the sum of equity and net debt. Management examines this ratio to assess how well it is using its funds to generate returns. We believe that this measure is useful to investors for
	the same reasons.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:12PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#991F3D">
<B>
<A NAME="D228504D40F_HTM_AIF228504_31">
</A>
	Fiscal Year ended September&nbsp;30, 2016
</B>
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<I>
	Long-term Debt
</I>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	On November&nbsp;8, 2016, the unsecured committed revolving facility of $1,500&nbsp;million of the Company was extended by two years to December 2021 and
	can be further extended. There were no material changes in the terms and conditions including interest rates and banking covenants.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	For the year
	ended September&nbsp;30, 2016, $182.7&nbsp;million was used to reduce our outstanding long-term debt mainly driven by $129.7&nbsp;million in repayment under the term loan credit facility, while we made net repayments of $901.6&nbsp;million to reduce
	our long-term debt last year. During the years ended September&nbsp;30, 2016 and 2015, the Company used $24.1&nbsp;million and $121.6&nbsp;million respectively to settle the cross-currency swaps related to the outstanding long-term debt repaid
	during these periods. There is no outstanding amount under our revolving credit facility other than pursuant to letters of credit.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>

</B>
</P>

<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D228504D40F_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/12/21/0001193125-16-800302_G228504ANNINFO.JPG" ALT="LOGO">
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<I>
	Share Repurchase Program
</I>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	On January&nbsp;27, 2016, the Company&#146;s Board of Directors authorized and subsequently received the approval from the TSX for the renewal of its
	NCIB to purchase up to 21,425,992 Class&nbsp;A subordinate voting shares for cancellation, representing 10% of the Company&#146;s public float as of the close of business on January&nbsp;22, 2016. The Class&nbsp;A subordinate voting shares may be
	purchased under the NCIB between February&nbsp;11, 2016 and the earlier of February&nbsp;3, 2017 or the date on which the Company has either acquired the maximum number of Class&nbsp;A subordinate voting shares allowable under the NCIB, or elects to
	terminate the NCIB.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	During fiscal 2016, the Company repurchased 9,319,875 Class&nbsp;A subordinate voting shares for approximately
	$517.8&nbsp;million at an average price of $55.56 under the previous and current NCIB. The repurchased shares included 7,112,375 Class&nbsp;A subordinate voting shares repurchased from Caisse de d&eacute;p&ocirc;t et placement du Qu&eacute;bec (the
	&#147;Caisse&#148;) for cash consideration of $400.0&nbsp;million. In accordance with the TSX rules, the repurchase is considered in the annual aggregate limit that the Company is entitled to repurchase under its current NCIB. The NCIB allows for
	purchases outside of the facilities of the TSX by private agreements pursuant to exemption orders issued by securities regulatory authorities. As at September&nbsp;30, 2016, the Company could repurchase up to 14,313,617 Class&nbsp;A subordinate
	voting shares under the current NCIB.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<I>
	Bookings and
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	Book-To-Bill
</FONT>
</FONT>
	Ratio
</I>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Bookings for the year were $11.7&nbsp;billion representing a
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	book-to-bill
</FONT>
</FONT>
	ratio of 109.8%. Of the $11.7&nbsp;billion in bookings signed during this year, 43% came from new business, while 57% came from extensions and renewals.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Our largest verticals for bookings were Government, MRD and Financial services, making up approximately 33%, 30% and 20% of total bookings, respectively.
	From a reporting segment perspective, the U.S. accounted for 25% of total bookings, followed by Canada at 21% and the Nordics at 15%.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Information
	regarding our bookings is a key indicator of the volume of our business over time. However, due to the timing and transition period associated with outsourcing contracts, the realization of revenue related to these bookings may fluctuate from period
	to period. The values initially booked may change over time due to their variable attributes, including demand-driven usage, modifications in the scope of work to be performed caused by changes in client requirements as well as termination clauses
	at the option of the client. As such, information regarding our bookings is not comparable to, nor should it be substituted for an analysis of our revenue; it is instead a key indicator of our future revenue used by the Company&#146;s management to
	measure growth.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<I>
	Foreign currency impact
</I>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Foreign currency
	rate fluctuations favourably impacted our revenue by 3.7%. This compares with a favourable impact of 2.0% in fiscal 2015 and a favourable impact of 7.0% in fiscal 2014.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>

</P>
