<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Valuation techniques used to value financial instruments are as follows:
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
	-
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
	The fair value of Senior U.S. and euro unsecured notes, the unsecured committed term loan credit facility and the other
	long-term debt is estimated by discounting expected cash flows at rates currently offered to the Company for debts of the same remaining maturities and conditions;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
	-
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
	The fair value of long-term bonds included in funds held for clients and in long-term investments is determined by
	discounting the future cash flows using observable inputs, such as interest rate yield curves or credit spreads, or according to similar transactions on an
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	arm&#146;s-length
</FONT>
	basis;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
	-
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
	The fair value of foreign currency forward contracts is determined using forward exchange rates at the end of the
	reporting period;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
	-
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
	The fair value of cross-currency swaps and interest rate swaps is determined based on market data (primarily yield
	curves, exchange rates and interest rates) to calculate the present value of all estimated flows;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
	-
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
	The fair value of cash and cash equivalents is determined using observable quotes.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	As at September&nbsp;30, 2016, there were no changes in valuation techniques.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company expects that approximately $18,530,000 of the accumulated net unrealized gain on derivative financial instruments designated as cash flow
	hedges as at September&nbsp;30, 2016 will be reclassified in the consolidated statements of earnings in the next 12 months.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	During the year ended
	September&nbsp;30, 2016, the Company&#146;s hedging relationships were effective.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	MARKET RISK
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Market risk incorporates a range of risks. Movements in risk factors, such as interest rate risk and currency risk, affect the fair values of financial
	assets and liabilities.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	Interest rate risk
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company has
	interest rate swaps whereby the Company receives a fixed rate of interest and pays interest at a variable rate on the notional amount of a portion of its Senior U.S. unsecured notes. These swaps are being used to hedge the exposure to changes in the
	fair value of the debt.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company was also exposed to interest rate risk on its unsecured committed term loan credit facility and held interest
	rate swaps that mitigated this risk on a portion of that debt. Under these interest rate swaps, the Company received a variable rate of interest and paid interest at a fixed rate on the notional amount. Following the repayment of this debt during
	the year ended September&nbsp;30, 2016, the Company settled the related
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	floating-to-fixed
</FONT>
</FONT>
	interest rate swap with a notional amount of $109,730,000 (Note 13).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company analyzes its interest rate risk exposure on an ongoing basis using various scenarios to simulate refinancing or the renewal of existing
	positions. Based on these scenarios, a change in the interest rate of 1% would not have had a significant impact on net earnings and comprehensive income.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:18PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW" ALIGN="RIGHT">
<FONT COLOR="#AAACAC">
	109
</FONT>
</P>

	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:18PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#9C9D9D">
	Notes
	to the Consolidated Financial Statements
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	For the years ended September 30, 2016 and 2015
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	(tabular amounts only are in thousands of Canadian dollars, except per share data)
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:12PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="7%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<B>
	30.
</B>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<B>
	Financial instruments (continued)
</B>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	MARKET
	RISK (CONTINUED)
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	Currency risk
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company operates internationally and is exposed to risk from changes in foreign
	currency exchange rates. The Company mitigates this risk principally through foreign currency denominated debt and derivative financial instruments. The Company uses the following derivative financial instruments which are foreign currency forward
	contracts to hedge contractual cash flows or forecasted cash flows in currencies other than the functional currency of its subsidiaries.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company
	hedges a portion of the translation of the Company&#146;s net investments in its U.S. and European operations into Canadian dollar with unsecured committed term loan credit facility, Senior U.S. and euro unsecured notes. The Company also hedges a
	portion of the translation of the Company&#146;s net investments in its European operations with cross-currency swaps.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	During the year ended
	September&nbsp;30, 2016, the Company entered into Canadian dollar to euro cross-currency swap agreements for a notional amount of $831,400,000 designated as hedging instruments of the Company&#146;s net investment in European operations.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	During the year ended September&nbsp;30, 2016, the Company settled cross-currency swaps with a notional amount of $109,730,000 ($859,070,000 for the year
	ended September&nbsp;30, 2015) for a net amount of $24,057,000 ($121,615,000 for the year ended September&nbsp;30, 2015). The loss on settlements was recognized in other comprehensive income and will be transferred to earnings when the net
	investment is disposed of.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	During the year ended September&nbsp;30, 2016, the Company has entered into cross-currency swap agreements, for a notional
	amount of U.S.$600,000,000, related to its Senior U.S. unsecured notes. The cross-currency swaps are designated as cash flow hedges to offset the variability in the exchange rate between the U.S. and Canadian dollar.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company has also entered into foreign currency forward contracts to hedge the variability in various foreign currency exchange rates on future
	revenues.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Hedging relationships are designated and documented at inception and quarterly effectiveness assessments are performed during the year.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company is mainly exposed to fluctuations in the Swedish krona, the U.S. dollar, the euro and the British pound. The following table details the
	Company&#146;s sensitivity to a 10% strengthening of the Swedish krona, the U.S. dollar, the euro and the British pound foreign currency rates on net earnings and comprehensive income against the Canadian dollar. The sensitivity analysis on net
	earnings presents the impact of foreign currency denominated financial instruments and adjusts their translation at period end for a 10% strengthening in foreign currency rates. The sensitivity analysis on other comprehensive income presents the
	impact of a 10% strengthening in foreign currency rates on the fair value of foreign currency forward contracts designated as cash flow hedges and on net investment hedges.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>

<FONT COLOR="#9C9D9D">
	Notes
	to the Consolidated Financial Statements
</FONT>

	For the years ended September 30, 2016 and 2015

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	LIQUIDITY RISK
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Liquidity risk is the risk that the Company is
	not able to meet its financial obligations as they fall due or can do so only at excessive cost. The Company&#146;s activities are financed through a combination of the cash flows from operations, borrowing under existing credit facilities, the
	issuance of debt and the issuance of equity. One of management&#146;s primary goals is to maintain an optimal level of liquidity through the active management of the assets and liabilities as well as the cash flows.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The following table summarizes the carrying amount and the contractual maturities of both the interest and principal portion of significant financial
	liabilities. All amounts contractually denominated in foreign currency are presented in Canadian dollar equivalent amounts using the
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	period-end
</FONT>
	spot rate.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	As at September&nbsp;30, 2016, the Company held cash and cash equivalents and long-term investments of $623,775,000
	($347,464,000 as at September&nbsp;30, 2015). The Company also had available $1,466,086,000 in unsecured committed revolving credit facility ($1,456,776,000 as at September&nbsp;30, 2015). The funds held for clients of $369,530,000 ($496,397,000 as
	at September&nbsp;30, 2015) fully covered the clients&#146; funds obligations. As at September&nbsp;30, 2016, trade accounts receivable amounted to $816,885,000 ($889,192,000 as at September&nbsp;30, 2015). Given the Company&#146;s available liquid
	resources as compared to the timing of the payments of liabilities, management assesses the Company&#146;s liquidity risk to be low.
</P>

</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company takes on exposure to
	credit risk, which is the risk that a counterparty will be unable to pay amounts in full when due. Financial instruments that potentially subject the Company to concentrations of credit risk consist of cash and cash equivalents, accounts receivable
	and long-term investments. The maximum exposure of credit risk is generally represented by the carrying amount of these items reported on the consolidated balance sheets.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company is exposed to credit risk in connection with long-term investments through the possible inability of borrowers to meet the terms of their
	obligations. The Company mitigates this risk by investing primarily in high credit quality corporate and government bonds with a credit rating of A or higher.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company has accounts receivable derived from clients engaged in various industries including governmental agencies, finance, telecommunications,
	manufacturing and utilities that are not concentrated in any specific geographic area. These specific industries may be affected by economic factors that may impact trade accounts receivable. However, management does not believe that the Company is
	subject to any significant credit risk in view of the Company&#146;s large and diversified client base. Overall, management does not believe that any single industry or geographic region represents a significant credit risk to the Company.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The following table sets forth details of the age of trade accounts receivable that are past due:
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The carrying amount of trade accounts receivable is reduced by an allowance account and the amount of the loss is
	recognized in the consolidated statements of earnings within costs of services, selling and administrative. When a receivable balance is considered uncollectible, it is written off against the allowance for doubtful accounts. Subsequent recoveries
	of amounts previously written off are credited against costs of services, selling and administrative in the consolidated statements of earnings.
</P>

	&nbsp;

<A HREF="#D228504D40F_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW">
<FONT COLOR="#A7A9AB">
<B>
	CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:24PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:18PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<FONT COLOR="#9C9D9D">
	Notes to the Consolidated Financial Statements
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	For the years ended September 30, 2016 and 2015
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	(tabular amounts only are in thousands of Canadian dollars, except per share data)
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:12PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="7%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<B>
	31.
</B>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<B>
	Capital risk management
</B>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company is exposed to risks of varying degrees of significance which
	could affect its ability to achieve its strategic objectives for growth. The main objectives of the Company&#146;s risk management process are to ensure that risks are properly identified and that the capital base is adequate in relation to these
	risks.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company manages its capital to ensure that there are adequate capital resources while maximizing the return to shareholders through the
	optimization of the debt and equity balance. As at September&nbsp;30, 2016, total managed capital was $8,999,358,000 ($8,556,720,000 as at September&nbsp;30, 2015). Managed capital consists of long-term debt, including the current portion (Note 13),
	cash and cash equivalents, long-term investments (Note 10) and shareholders&#146; equity. The basis for the Company&#146;s capital structure is dependent on the Company&#146;s expected business growth and changes in the business environment. When
	capital needs have been specified, the Company&#146;s management proposes capital transactions for the approval of the Company&#146;s Audit and Risk Management Committee and Board of Directors. The capital risk policy remains unchanged from prior
	periods.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company monitors its capital by reviewing various financial metrics, including the following:
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
	-
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
	Net Debt/Capitalization
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
	-
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
	Debt/EBITDA
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Net debt, capitalization and EBITDA are additional measures. Net debt represents debt
	(including the current portion and the fair value of derivative financial instruments) less cash and cash equivalents and long-term investments. Capitalization is shareholders&#146; equity plus debt. EBITDA is calculated as earnings from continuing
	operations before income taxes, finance costs, depreciation, amortization and restructuring costs. The Company believes that the results of the current internal ratios are consistent with its capital management objectives.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company is subject to external covenants on its Senior U.S. and euro unsecured notes and unsecured committed term loan credit facility. The ratios are
	as follows:
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
	-
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
	A leverage ratio, which is the ratio of total debt to EBITDA for the four most recent quarters
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	1
</SUP>
	.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
	-
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
	An interest and rent coverage ratio, which is the ratio of the EBITDAR for the four most recent quarters to the total
	finance costs and the operating rentals in the same periods. EBITDAR, a
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	non-GAAP
</FONT>
	measure, is calculated as EBITDA before rent expense
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	1
</SUP>
	.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
	-
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
	In the case of the Senior U.S. and euro unsecured notes, a minimum net worth is required, whereby shareholders&#146;
	equity, excluding foreign exchange translation adjustments included in accumulated other comprehensive income, cannot be less than a specified threshold.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	These ratios are calculated on a consolidated basis.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company is in compliance with these covenants and monitors them on an ongoing basis. The ratios are also reviewed quarterly by the Company&#146;s
	Audit and Risk Management Committee. The Company is not subject to any other externally imposed capital requirements.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:7PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	1
</SUP>
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:7PT">
	In the event of an acquisition, the available historical financial information of the acquired Company will be used in
	the computation of the ratios.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:18PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW">
<FONT COLOR="#8B8D90">
	Management&#146;s Discussion and Analysis
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:30PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:8PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	November&nbsp;9, 2016
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:24PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:12PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	Basis of Presentation
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:8PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	This Management&#146;s
	Discussion and Analysis of the Financial Position and Results of Operations (&#147;MD&amp;A&#148;) is the responsibility of management and has been reviewed and approved by the Board of Directors. This MD&amp;A has been prepared in accordance with
	the requirements of the Canadian Securities Administrators. The Board of Directors is ultimately responsible for reviewing and approving the MD&amp;A. The Board of Directors carries out this responsibility mainly through its Audit and Risk
	Management Committee, which is appointed by the Board of Directors and is comprised entirely of independent and financially literate directors.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:8PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Throughout this document, CGI Group Inc. is referred to as &#147;CGI&#148;, &#147;we&#148;, &#147;our&#148; or &#147;Company&#148;. This MD&amp;A provides
	information management believes is relevant to an assessment and understanding of the consolidated results of operations and financial condition of the Company. This document should be read in conjunction with the audited consolidated financial
	statements and the notes thereto for the years ended September&nbsp;30, 2016 and 2015. CGI&#146;s accounting policies are in accordance with International Financial Reporting Standards (&#147;IFRS&#148;) as issued by the International Accounting
	Standards Board (&#147;IASB&#148;). All dollar amounts are in Canadian dollars unless otherwise indicated.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:24PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:12PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	Materiality of Disclosures
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:8PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	This MD&amp;A includes information we believe is material to investors. We consider something to be material if it results in, or would reasonably be
	expected to result in, a significant change in the market price or value of our shares, or if it is likely that a reasonable investor would consider the information to be important in making an investment decision.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:24PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:12PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">

	the United States Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended, and are &#147;forward-looking information&#148; within the meaning of Canadian securities laws. These statements and this information represent CGI&#146;s intentions, plans, expectations
	and beliefs, and are subject to risks, uncertainties and other factors, of which many are beyond the control of the Company. These factors could cause actual results to differ materially from such forward-looking statements or forward-looking
	information. These factors include but are not restricted to: the timing and size of new contracts; acquisitions and other corporate developments; the ability to attract and retain qualified employees; market competition in the rapidly evolving
	information technology industry; general economic and business conditions; foreign exchange and other risks identified in the MD&amp;A and in other public disclosure documents filed with the Canadian securities authorities (filed on SEDAR at

	which they are made. In particular, statements relating to future performance are forward-looking statements and forward-looking information. CGI disclaims any intention or obligation to publicly update or revise any forward-looking statements or
	forward-looking information, whether as a result of new information, future events or otherwise, except as required by applicable law. Readers are cautioned not to place undue reliance on these forward-looking statements or on this forward-looking
	information. You will find more information about the risks that could cause our actual results to differ significantly from our current expectations in section 10 &#150; Risk Environment.

	MANAGEMENT&#146;S DISCUSSION AND ANALYSIS
</B>
</FONT>

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:24PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:12PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	Non-GAAP and Key Performance Measures
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The reader should note that the Company reports its financial results in accordance with IFRS. However, we use a combination of financial measures,
	ratios, and non-GAAP measures to assess our Company&#146;s performance. The non-GAAP measures used in this MD&amp;A do not have any standardized meaning prescribed by IFRS and are therefore unlikely to be comparable to similar measures presented by
	other issuers. These measures should be considered as supplemental in nature and not as a substitute for the related financial information prepared in accordance with IFRS.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The table below summarizes our non-GAAP measures and most relevant key performance measures:
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<A NAME="FIS_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE_131"></A>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT" ALIGN="CENTER">

</TD>

<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-TOP:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-LEFT:8PT" BGCOLOR="#BCBCBC">
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
	Profitability&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PX SOLID #000000">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PX SOLID #000000">
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:4PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#149;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PX SOLID #000000">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-RIGHT:8PT">
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Adjusted EBIT (non-GAAP) &#150; is a measure of earnings excluding restructuring costs, net finance costs and income tax expense as these items are not
	directly related to the cost of operations. Management believes this measure is useful to investors as it best reflects the Company&#146;s operating profitability and allows for better comparability from period to period as well as to trend analysis
	in our operations. A reconciliation of the adjusted EBIT to its closest IFRS measure can be found in section 3.7 of the present document.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT" ALIGN="LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-LEFT:8PT" BGCOLOR="#BCBCBC">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#149;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-RIGHT:8PT">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Net earnings &#150; is a measure of earnings generated for shareholders.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT" ALIGN="LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-LEFT:8PT" BGCOLOR="#BCBCBC">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#149;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-RIGHT:8PT">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Diluted earnings per share &#150; is a measure of earnings generated for
	shareholders on a per share basis, assuming all dilutive elements are exercised.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT" ALIGN="LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-LEFT:8PT" BGCOLOR="#BCBCBC">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#149;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-RIGHT:8PT">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Net earnings excluding specific items (non-GAAP) &#150; is a measure of net
	earnings excluding certain items not considered by management to be part of the day to day operations. By excluding these items, it provides a better evaluation of operating performance using the same measures as management. Management believes
	that, as a result, the investors are afforded greater transparency in assessing the true operation performance of the Company also providing better comparability from period to period. A reconciliation of the net earnings excluding specific items to
	its closest IFRS measure can be found in section 3.8.3. of the present document.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT" ALIGN="LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-LEFT:8PT" BGCOLOR="#BCBCBC">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#149;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-RIGHT:8PT">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Basic and diluted earnings per share
	excluding specific items (non-GAAP) &#150; is defined as the net earnings excluding specific items (non-GAAP) on a per share basis. Management believes that this measure is useful to investors as it best reflects the Company&#146;s operating
	profitability on a per share basis and allows for better comparability from period to period. The basic and diluted earnings per share reported in accordance with IFRS can be found in section 3.8 of the present document while the basic and diluted
	earnings per share excluding specific items can be found in section 3.8.3.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT" ALIGN="LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-LEFT:8PT" BGCOLOR="#BCBCBC">
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
	Liquidity
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#149;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-RIGHT:8PT">
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Cash
	provided by operating activities &#150; is a measure of cash generated from managing our day-to-day business operations. We believe strong operating cash flow is indicative of financial flexibility, allowing us to execute our Company&#146;s
	strategy.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT" ALIGN="LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-LEFT:8PT" BGCOLOR="#BCBCBC">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#149;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-RIGHT:8PT">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Days sales outstanding (&#147;DSO&#148;)
	(non-GAAP) &#150; is the average number of days needed to convert our trade receivables and work in progress into cash. DSO is obtained by subtracting deferred revenue from trade accounts receivable and work in progress; the result is divided by the
	quarter&#146;s revenue over 90 days. Deferred revenue is net of the fair value adjustments on revenue-generating contracts established upon a business combination. Management tracks this metric closely to ensure timely collection, healthy liquidity,
	and is committed to a DSO target of 45 days or less. We believe this measure is useful to investors as it demonstrates the Company&#146;s ability to timely convert its trade receivables and work in progress into cash.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT" ALIGN="LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Constant currency growth (non-GAAP) &#150; is a measure of revenue growth before foreign currency impacts. This growth is calculated by translating
	current period results in local currency using the conversion rates in the equivalent period from the prior year. Management believes that it is helpful to adjust revenue to exclude the impact of currency fluctuations to facilitate period-to-period
	comparisons of business performance. We believe that this measure is useful to investors for the same reason.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT" ALIGN="LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-LEFT:8PT" BGCOLOR="#BCBCBC">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#149;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-RIGHT:8PT">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Backlog (non-GAAP) &#150; includes new contract wins, extensions and renewals
	(&#147;bookings&#148;(non-GAAP)), partially offset by the backlog consumed during the period as a result of client work performed and adjustments related to the volume, cancellation and the impact of foreign currencies to our existing contracts.
	Backlog incorporates estimates from management that are subject to change. Management tracks this measure as it is a key indicator of management&#146;s best estimate of revenue to be realized in the future and believes that this measure is useful to
	investors for the same reason.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT" ALIGN="LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-LEFT:8PT" BGCOLOR="#BCBCBC">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#149;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-RIGHT:8PT">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Book-to-bill ratio (non-GAAP) &#150; is a
	measure of the proportion of the value of our bookings to our revenue in the period. This metric allows management to monitor the Company&#146;s business development efforts to ensure we grow our backlog and our business over time and believes that
	this measure is useful to investors for the same reason. Management remains committed to maintaining a target ratio greater than 100% over a trailing 12-month period. Management believes that a longer period is a more representative measure as the
	services and contract type, size and timing of bookings could cause this measurement to fluctuate significantly if taken for only a three-month period.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT" ALIGN="LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-LEFT:8PT" BGCOLOR="#BCBCBC">
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Capital Structure
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#149;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-RIGHT:8PT">
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Net debt
	(non-GAAP) &#150; is obtained by subtracting from our debt our cash and cash equivalents, short- term investments, long-term investments and fair value of foreign currency derivative financial instruments related to debt. Management uses the net
	debt metric to monitor the Company&#146;s financial leverage. We believe that this metric is useful to investors as it provides insight into our financial strength. A reconciliation of net debt to its closest IFRS measure can be found in section 4.5
	of the present document.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT" ALIGN="LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-LEFT:8PT" BGCOLOR="#BCBCBC">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#149;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-RIGHT:8PT">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Net debt to capitalization ratio (non-GAAP) &#150; is a measure of our level
	of financial leverage and is obtained by dividing the net debt by the sum of shareholder&#146;s equity and debt. Management uses the net debt to capitalization metric to monitor the proportion of debt versus capital used to finance our operations
	and to assess the Company&#146;s financial strength. We believe that this metric is useful to investors as it provides insight into our financial strength.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT" ALIGN="LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-LEFT:8PT" BGCOLOR="#BCBCBC">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#149;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-RIGHT:8PT">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Return on equity (&#147;ROE&#148;) (non-GAAP) &#150; is a measure of the rate
	of return on the ownership interest of our shareholders and is calculated as the proportion of earnings for the last 12 months over the last four quarters&#146; average equity. Management looks at ROE to measure its efficiency at generating earnings
	for the Company&#146;s shareholders and how well the Company uses the invested funds to generate earnings growth. We believe that this measure is useful to investors for the same reasons.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT" ALIGN="LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-LEFT:8PT" BGCOLOR="#BCBCBC">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#149;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-RIGHT:8PT">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Return on invested capital (&#147;ROIC&#148;)
	(non-GAAP) &#150; is a measure of the Company&#146;s efficiency at allocating the capital under its control to profitable investments and is calculated as the proportion of the after-tax adjusted EBIT for the last 12 months, over the last four
	quarters&#146; average invested capital, which is defined as the sum of equity and net debt. Management examines this ratio to assess how well it is using its funds to generate returns. We believe that this measure is useful to investors for the
	same reason.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT" ALIGN="LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:16PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:12PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	Reporting segments
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The
	Company&#146;s operations are managed through the following seven operating segments, referred to as our Strategic Business Units, namely: United States of America (&#147;U.S.&#148;); Nordics; Canada; France (including Luxembourg and Morocco)
	(&#147;France&#148;); United Kingdom (&#147;U.K.&#148;); Eastern, Central and Southern Europe (primarily Netherlands and Germany) (&#147;ECS&#148;); and Asia Pacific (including Australia, India and the Philippines) (&#147;Asia Pacific&#148;). Please
	refer to sections 3.4 and 3.6 of the present document and to note 27 of our audited consolidated financial statements for additional information on our segments.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:18PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW" ALIGN="RIGHT">
<FONT COLOR="#A7A9AB">
	3
</FONT>
</P>

<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-LEFT:8PT" BGCOLOR="#BCBCBC">
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:4PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT; MARGIN-LEFT:2.30EM; TEXT-INDENT:-2.30EM; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Corporate
<BR>
	&nbsp;Overview
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:4PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	A description of our business and how we generate revenue as well
	as the markets in which we operate.
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000">
	&nbsp;

<TR STYLE="FONT-SIZE:1PT">
<TD HEIGHT="10" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-LEFT:8PT" BGCOLOR="#BCBCBC">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="10" COLSPAN="2">
</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="10" COLSPAN="2">
</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="10" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000">
	&nbsp;

<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-LEFT:8PT" BGCOLOR="#BCBCBC">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:3.00EM; TEXT-INDENT:-3.00EM; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	1.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;About CGI
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT" ALIGN="LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>

</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000">

<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-RIGHT:8PT">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="CENTER">
	6
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT" ALIGN="LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-LEFT:8PT" BGCOLOR="#BCBCBC">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:3.00EM; TEXT-INDENT:-3.00EM; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	1.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Vision and Strategy
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT" ALIGN="LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-RIGHT:8PT">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="CENTER">
	7
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:1PT" ALIGN="LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1PX SOLID #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000; PADDING-LEFT:8PT" BGCOLOR="#BCBCBC">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PX SOLID #000000">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;

<EFX_MANAGEMENTS_DISCUSSION>
<A NAME="FIS_MANAGEMENTS_DISCUSSION_4"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW">
<FONT COLOR="#A7A9AB">
<B>
	MANAGEMENT&#146;S DISCUSSION AND ANALYSIS
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:24PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:12PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<B>
	1.
</B>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<B>
	Corporate Overview
</B>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:2.0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:2PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:2.00PT SOLID #000000">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	1.1. ABOUT CGI
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Founded in 1976 and headquartered in Montr&eacute;al, Canada, CGI is among the largest Information Technology (&#147;IT&#148;) and business process
	service providers in the world, with approximately 68,000 professionals. Through high-end consulting, systems integration, transformational outsourcing and Intellectual Property (&#147;IP&#148;) solutions, combined with in-depth industry expertise,
	CGI works with clients across the globe through a unique client proximity and best-fit global delivery model to accelerate their digital transformation and drive competitive advantage.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	End-to-end services
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	CGI delivers end-to-end services that
	cover the full spectrum of delivery; from solution design and development, to implementation, integration and technology operations. Our portfolio encompasses:
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<B>
	&#149;
</B>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<B>
	High-end consulting and system integration:
</B>
	CGI helps clients form their digital roadmap, adopting an agile,
	iterative approach that enables them to innovate, connect and rationalize legacy systems to deliver enterprise-wide change.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<B>
	&#149;
</B>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT">
<B>
	Transformational outsourcing:
</B>
	Our clients entrust us with full or partial responsibility for their IT and business
	functions. In return, we deliver significant efficiency improvements and cost savings. Typical services in an end-to-end engagement include: application development, integration and maintenance; technology infrastructure management; and business
	process services, such as collections and payroll management. Outsourcing contracts are long term in nature, with a typical duration of 5 to 10 or more years, allowing our clients to reinvest savings, further driving digital transformation.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	Deep industry expertise
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	CGI has long
	and focused practices in all of our core industries, providing clients with a partner that is not only expert in IT, but expert in their industries. This combination of business knowledge and digital technology expertise allows us to help our
	clients adapt as their industries change and, in the process, allows us to evolve the industries in which we operate.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Our targeted industries
	include: government, financial services, health, utilities, telecommunications, oil&nbsp;&amp; gas, manufacturing, retail&nbsp;&amp; consumer services, transportation and post&nbsp;&amp; logistics. While these represent our go-to-market industry
	targets, we group these industries into the following: government; financial services; health; telecommunications&nbsp;&amp; utilities; and manufacturing, retail&nbsp;&amp; distribution (&#147;MRD&#148;).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	As the move toward digitalization continues to increase across industries, CGI partners with clients to support their strategic initiatives. We provide
	extensive industry expertise to guide them in becoming customer-centric digital organizations.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	Digital IP solutions
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	CGI&#146;s comprehensive portfolio of IP solutions support our clients&#146; mission-critical business functions and accelerate their digital
	transformation. We offer more than 150 IP-based solutions for the industries we serve, as well as cross-industry solutions. These solutions include digital-enabling software applications, reusable frameworks and innovative delivery methodologies -
	like Software as a Service.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	Client-inspired innovation
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	CGI is a trusted partner with more than 40 years of experience in delivering innovative, client-inspired business services and solutions. Through
	innovation programs and investments, CGI supports clients with their most strategic initiatives. We help develop, innovate and protect the technology that enables clients to achieve their digital transformation goals faster with reduced risk and
	enduring results.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	Quality processes
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	CGI clients expect
	consistency of service wherever and whenever they engage us. We have an outstanding track record of on-time, within-budget delivery as a result of our commitment to excellence and our robust governance model - the CGI Management Foundation. The CGI
	Management Foundation provides a common business language, frameworks and
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:18PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW">

	RESULTS
</FONT>

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:24PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	practices for managing all operations consistently across the globe, driving a
	focus on continuous improvement. We also invest in rigorous quality and service delivery standards (including ISO and Capability Maturity Model Integration (&#147;CMMI&#148;) certification programs), as well as a comprehensive Client Satisfaction
	Assessment Program, to ensure high client satisfaction on an ongoing basis.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	1.2. VISION AND STRATEGY
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	CGI is unique compared to most companies. We not only have a vision, but also a dream:
<I>
	&#147;To create an environment in which we enjoy working
	together and, as owners, contribute to building a company we can be proud of.&#148;
</I>
	This dream has motivated us since our founding in 1976 and drives our vision: &#147;
<I>
	To
</I>
<I>
	be a global, world-class information technology and business
	process services leader helping our clients succeed.
</I>
	&#148;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	In pursuing this dream and vision, CGI has been highly disciplined throughout its
	history in executing a Build and Buy profitable growth strategy comprised of four pillars that combine profitable organic growth (Build) and accretive acquisitions (Buy):
<B>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:3%; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<B>
	Pillar 1:
</B>
	Smaller contract wins, renewals and extensions
<B>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:3%; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<B>
	Pillar 2:
</B>
	Large, long-term transformational outsourcing contracts
<B>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:3%; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<B>
	Pillar 3:
</B>
	Small firm or niche player acquisitions
<B>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:3%; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<B>
	Pillar 4:
</B>
	Large, transformational acquisitions
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The first two pillars relate to driving profitable organic growth through the pursuit of contracts - both large and small - with new and existing clients
	in our targeted industries.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The last two pillars focus on growth through niche and large acquisitions. We identify niche acquisitions through a
	strategic qualification process that systematically searches for targets to strengthen our local proximity in metro markets, our industry expertise and enhance our services and solutions. We also pursue large acquisitions to further expand our
	geographic presence and critical mass, which enables us to compete for large outsourcing contracts and broaden our client relationships. CGI will continue to be a consolidator in the IT services industry.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Since 1976, our professionals have been working toward the same dream and vision. Today, with a presence in hundreds of global locations and more than
	$10 billion in revenue, our aspiration is to double our size over a 5 to 7 year period.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	Executing our strategy
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	CGI&#146;s strategy is executed through a unique business model that combines client proximity with an extensive global delivery network to deliver the
	following benefits:
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>

	Local responsiveness and accountability:
</B>
	We live and work near our clients to provide a high level of
	responsiveness. Our local CGI teams speak our clients&#146; language, understand their business environment, and collaborate to meet their goals and advance their business.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW">
<FONT COLOR="#A7A9AB">
<B>
	MANAGEMENT&#146;S DISCUSSION AND ANALYSIS
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:24PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	1.3. COMPETITIVE ENVIRONMENT
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	In today&#146;s digital era, there is a competitive urgency for organizations across industries to become digital in a sustainable way. The pressure is
	on to modernize legacy assets and connect them to digital business and operating models. Central to this massive transformation is the evolving role of technology. Traditionally viewed as an enabler, technology is now being recognized as a business
	driver. The promise of digital creates an enormous opportunity to transform organizations end-to-end, and CGI is well-positioned to serve as a digital partner and expert of choice. We&#146;re working with clients across the globe to implement
	digital strategies, roadmaps and solutions that revolutionize the customer/citizen experience, drive the launch of new products and services, and deliver efficiencies and cost savings.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	As the demand for digitalization increases, competition within the global IT industry is intensifying. CGI&#146;s competition comprises a variety of
	players; from niche companies providing specialized services and software, to global, end-to-end IT service providers, to large consulting firms. All of these players are competing to deliver some or all of the services we provide. Many factors
	distinguish the industry leaders, including the following:
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:9PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

	with respect to all of these factors. We&#146;re not only delivering all of the capabilities clients need to compete in a digital world, but the immediate results and long-term value they expect. We&#146;re helping clients to better run, change and

</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:7PT">
	Constant currency growth is adjusted to remove the impact of foreign currency exchange rate fluctuations. Please refer to
	section 3.4 for details.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:7PT" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	2
</SUP>
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY" STYLE=" MARGIN-TOP:0PT ; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:7PT">
	Adjusted EBIT is a measure for which we provide the reconciliation to its closest IFRS measure in section 3.7. For the
	year ended September&nbsp;30, 2014, adjusted EBIT excludes integration-related costs related to the restructuring and transformation of the operations of Logica plc (&#147;Logica&#148;) to the CGI model.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:2PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>

	Net earnings excluding specific items is a measure for which we provide the reconciliation to its closest IFRS measure in
	section 3.8.3 for the years ended September&nbsp;30, 2016 and 2015. For the year ended September&nbsp;30, 2014 specific items includes integration-related costs and resolution of acquisition- related provisions net of taxes as well as tax
	adjustments. Resolution of acquisition-related provisions came from adjustments of provisions that were established as part of the purchase price allocation for the Logica acquisition. Subsequent to the finalization of the purchase price allocation,
	such adjustments flow through the statement of earnings.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

</EFX_MANAGEMENTS_DISCUSSION>
<EFX_MANAGEMENTS_DISCUSSION>
<A NAME="FIS_MANAGEMENTS_DISCUSSION_7"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW">
<FONT COLOR="#A7A9AB">
<B>
	MANAGEMENT&#146;S DISCUSSION AND ANALYSIS
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:24PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	2.3.2. Share Repurchase Program
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	On January&nbsp;27, 2016, the Company&#146;s Board of Directors authorized and subsequently received the approval from the TSX for the renewal of the
	Normal Course Issuer Bid (&#147;NCIB&#148;) to purchase up to 21,425,992 Class&nbsp;A subordinate voting shares for cancellation, representing 10% of the Company&#146;s public float as of the close of business on January&nbsp;22, 2016. The
	Class&nbsp;A subordinate voting shares may be purchased under the NCIB commencing February&nbsp;11, 2016 and ending on the earlier of February&nbsp;3, 2017 or the date on which the Company has either acquired the maximum number of Class&nbsp;A
	subordinate voting shares allowable under the NCIB, or elects to terminate the NCIB.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:11PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	During fiscal 2016, the Company repurchased 9,319,875
	Class&nbsp;A subordinate voting shares for approximately $517.8 million at an average price of $55.56 under the previous and current NCIB. The repurchased shares included 7,112,375 Class&nbsp;A subordinate voting shares repurchased from Caisse de
	d&eacute;p&ocirc;t et placement du Qu&eacute;bec for cash consideration of $400.0 million. In accordance with the TSX rules, the repurchase is considered in the annual aggregate limit that the Company is entitled to repurchase under its current
	NCIB. As at September&nbsp;30, 2016, the Company may repurchase up to 14,313,617 Class&nbsp;A subordinate voting shares under the current NCIB.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	2.3.3. Capital
	Stock and Options Outstanding
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The following table provides a summary of the Capital Stock and Options Outstanding as at November&nbsp;4, 2016:
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<A NAME="FIS_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE_138"></A>
<DIV ALIGN="RIGHT">
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="81%">
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" WIDTH="1%">
</TD>
<TD WIDTH="18%">
</TD>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:10PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	2.4. INVESTMENTS IN SUBSIDIARIES
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:8PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	On November&nbsp;4, 2016, the Company announced the closing of the acquisition of Collaborative Consulting, a system integration and consulting company
	headquartered in Boston, Massachusetts. With approximately 400 professionals and annualized revenues of approximately US$76.0M, Collaborative Consulting will enhance and accelerate CGI&#146;s position as a provider of digital transformation
	services.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:8PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The cash acquisition of all unit holder positions of Collaborative Consulting was completed effective November&nbsp;3, 2016.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:18PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW">
<FONT COLOR="#A7A9AB">
	12
</FONT>
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage188"></A>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Information regarding our bookings is a key indicator of the volume of our business over time. However, due to the timing
	and transition period associated with outsourcing contracts, the realization of revenue related to these bookings may fluctuate from period to period. The values initially booked may change over time due to their variable attributes, including
	demand-driven usage, modifications in the scope of work to be performed caused by changes in client requirements as well as termination clauses at the option of the client. As such, information regarding our bookings is not comparable to, nor should
	it be substituted for an analysis of our revenue; it is instead a key indicator of our future revenue used by the Company&#146;s management to measure growth.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:8PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The following table provides a summary of the bookings and book-to-bill ratio by segment:

<EFX_MANAGEMENTS_DISCUSSION>
<A NAME="FIS_MANAGEMENTS_DISCUSSION_8"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW">
<FONT COLOR="#A7A9AB">
<B>
	MANAGEMENT&#146;S DISCUSSION AND ANALYSIS
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:24PT; MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	3.2. FOREIGN EXCHANGE
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:8PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The Company operates globally and is exposed to changes in foreign currency rates. Accordingly, as prescribed by IFRS, we value assets, liabilities and
	transactions that are measured in foreign currencies using various exchange rates. We report all dollar amounts in Canadian dollars.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<I>
	&nbsp;Closing foreign
	exchange rates
</I>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	3.3.1. Client Concentration
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	IFRS guidance on segment disclosures defines a single customer as a group of entities that are known to the reporting entity to be under common control.
	As a consequence, our work for the U.S. federal government including its various agencies represented 13.2% of our revenue for fiscal 2016 as compared to 14.0% in fiscal 2015.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:18PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW">
<FONT COLOR="#A7A9AB">
	14
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL">
<B>
	3.4. REVENUE VARIATION AND REVENUE BY SEGMENT
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:8PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	Our seven segments are reported based on where the client&#146;s work is delivered from - our geographic delivery model.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:8PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:9PT; FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
	The following table provides a summary of the year-over-year changes in our revenue, in total and by segment, separately showing the impacts of foreign
	currency exchange rate variations between fiscal 2016 and fiscal 2015. The fiscal 2015 revenue by segment was recorded reflecting the actual foreign exchange rates for that period. The foreign exchange impact is the difference between the current
	period&#146;s actual results and the same period&#146;s results converted with the prior year&#146;s foreign exchange rate.
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT">
	&nbsp;
